1. Download all the files I need from rscb.org.  

2. Find the residue to mutate. 
Command: press esc
Command: /[chain name]  [resid num]
Command: press n (to search forward)
Command: press N (to search backward)

3. Select a block of text for the residue name. 
Command: press esc
Command: press control v
Command: arrow over the block of text
Command: press c
Command: type what you now want in that place
Command: press esc

4. Edit the atom names based on the same amino acid. 
Tip: Add more lines if you have to. 

5. Change the angle and location of the atoms so nothing has exactly the same place. 

6. Renumber the residues. 
Command: gmx_mpi editconf -f [old_name].pdb -resnr [resid_num] -o [new_name].pdb


